text: Tatia Dumbadse (born 21 August 1998) is a Georgian footballer who plays as a midfielder. She has played officially for the senior Georgia women's national team. ==International career== Dumbadse capped for Georgia at senior level during the UEFA Women's Euro 2017 qualifying Group 6, in a 0–3 home loss to Northern Ireland on 24 October 2015 and a 0–4 away loss to Switzerland three days later. ==References== Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Women's association football midfielders Category:Women's footballers from Georgia (country) Category:Georgia (country) women's international footballers Category:Expatriate footballers from Georgia (country) Category:Expatriate sportspeople from Georgia (country) in the United States Category:Expatriate women's soccer players in the United States
